Step 1: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100
• From the income statement:
  Gross Profit = 1,641,807.77 
  Total Revenue = 8,361,807.77
• Calculation:
  Gross Profit Margin = (1,641,807.77 / 8,361,807.77) × 100 ≈ 19.64%

Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio.
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities
• From the cash flow statement and balance sheet:
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -4,900,875.61 
  Total Current Liabilities = 3,428,090.41
• Calculation:
  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -4,900,875.61 / 3,428,090.41 ≈ -1.43

Thus, the solution in the specified JSON format is:

{"solution": {"Gross Profit Margin": "19.64%", "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-1.43"}}
